Two pupils, 12 and 13 years of Chemelil B1 primary school on Saturday morning died on the spot after being hit by a speeding vehicle in chemelil area Muhoroni sub county within Kisumu. Their schoolmate survived the accident but sustained a fracture on the lower jaw and was rushed to Chemelil Dispensary. The 8am accident was confirmed by Muhoroni Ocpd David Miniu who noted that the pupils were walking to school when they were knocked by the speeding vehicle near their school. Miniu noted that after causing the accident, the driver tried to escape but instead he rammed on a motorcycle and in the process injured the rider, a passenger and a kid were injured "The motorcycle rider sustained injuries on the leg(cut), The woman passengers also sustained injuries on the right leg and her son 4 year old who also sustained injuries on both legs," he said. He noted that driver of the vehicle ran away and is still at large and the vehicle towed to Chemelil police post. The body of the two pupils were taken to Ahero Sub county hospital morgue.